President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. met with King Hamad bin Isa Al Khalifa of Bahrain in Jeddah. The President expressed gratitude for the longstanding strategic partnership with Bahrain, particularly its hosting of the U.S. Navy Forces Central Command/5th Fleet. Both leaders emphasized their commitment to strengthening defense, security, economic, commercial, and people-to-people ties. President Biden praised Bahrain's expanded relations with Israel through the Abraham Accords and the Negev process. They also discussed mutual efforts to promote regional integration and enhance security cooperation.